Cancel Invoice API
To send a Cancel Invoice request, send an HTTP DELETE request to the below URL with the required parameters: It’s also mandatory to pass your Hubtel POS Sales ID for Cancel Invoice requests in the endpoint. Find your POS Sales ID here.


API Endpoint	https://rip.hubtel.com/api/proxy/{POS_Sales_ID}/cancel-invoice/{recurringInvoiceId}
Request Type	DELETE
Content Type	JSON

REQUEST PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Requirement	Description
recurringInvoiceId	String	Mandatory	The unique ID used to identify the recurring invoice being verified. It is taken from the create invoice response.

RESPONSE PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Description
ResponseCode	String	The unique response code on the status of the transaction.
Message	String	The message accompanying the response code. This gives a brief description of the response from the API.

SAMPLE CANCEL INVOICE HTTP REQUEST
HTTP

copy
Copy
  DELETE /api/proxy/11684/cancel-invoice/0f84e20a2839482e807128e8c21d08d6 HTTP/1.1
  Host: rip.hubtel.com
  Accept: application/json
  Content-Type: application/json
  Authorization: Basic endjeOBiZHhza250f3=
  Cache-Control: no-cache

SAMPLE CANCEL INVOICE RESPONSE
200 OK

copy
